# List illegal configuration entries
com.foreach.across.IllegalConfiguration=\
  org.springframework.data.web.config.SpringDataWebConfiguration->AcrossContext:spring-data,\
  org.springframework.cloud.openfeign.FeignClientFactoryBean->AcrossContext:spring-cloud-feign
#
# Illegal configuration descriptions.
#
com.foreach.across.IllegalConfiguration[spring-data].description=This is usually due to the use of @EnableSpringDataWebSupport on the application configuration, which is not compatible with Across applications.
com.foreach.across.IllegalConfiguration[spring-data].action=Simply remove the annotation altogether. Spring Data web support is usually activated automatically. If you want to use a custom configuration, ensure you add the configuration to the AcrossContextPostProcessorModule.
com.foreach.across.IllegalConfiguration[spring-cloud-feign].description=This is usually due to the use of @EnableFeignClients on the application configuration, which is not compatible with Across applications.
com.foreach.across.IllegalConfiguration[spring-cloud-feign].action=Move the annotation to a configuration class inside the desired Across modules that want to use Feign clients.
